  <h2>The conversation</h2>

  <p>Most young adults won&rsquo;t bring this up themselves. That&rsquo;s fine &mdash; this is a parent-initiated conversation. Keep it simple: &ldquo;Now that you&rsquo;re 18, we need to make sure that if anything ever happens to you, we can actually help. There are a few legal documents that make that possible. It takes about an hour of your time and then it&rsquo;s done.&rdquo;</p>

  <p>That&rsquo;s it. No drama. No morbid hypotheticals. Just a practical step that every adult &mdash; including brand-new ones &mdash; should have in place.</p>

